wxPython Cookbook
Chapter 12 Application Infrastructure,
           Building and Managing Applications for Distribution
Recipe 3 Using the SingleInstanceChecker

This is the example code for Recipe 3 Using the SingleInstanceChecker

Prerequisites:

1) Python 2.5 or 2.6 has been installed
2) wxPython 2.8 has been installed for the version of Python used above

How to run this script:

From the command line or your IDE run the following command

python singleinst.py

Then try to start another instance of the application from another console by
running the same command as above again. Observe that the original instance
will open a new window right after the second instance exits.
